{{expert-subject|Philosophy|ex2=Politics|date=February 2009}}
{{Forms of government}}
'''Ergatocracy''' (from the [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] word [[wikt:ἐργάτης|ἐργάτης]], ''ergates'', "worker" and the suffix [[wikt:-cracy|-cracy]], "government") is a type of government dominated by the labour and solidarities similar to [[communist]] beliefs. It refers to a society ruled by the working class. The term was coined by [[Eden Paul|Eden]] and [[Cedar Paul]] in their book ''Creative Revolution: A Study of Communist Ergatocracy''.<ref name=Paul>{{cite book|last1=Paul|first1=Cedar|last2=Paul|first2=Eden|title=Creative revolution:|date=1920|publisher=Thomas Seltzer|location=new York|url=https://archive.org/details/creativerevoluti00paul|accessdate=30 May 2015}}</ref><ref>https://bogdanovlibrary.files.wordpress.com/2016/08/2016-08-14-biggart-bogdanov-kultintern.pdf</ref>

