'''Flexblue''' is a concept of a small [[nuclear power plant]] (50 to 250 MWe), measuring a hundred meters long for about 14 meters in diameter. It is being studied by [[Naval Group]] (French industrial group specialised in naval defence and marine renewable energy) since 2008, in partnership with [[AREVA]], the [[French Alternative Energies and Atomic Energy Commission|CEA]] and [[Électricité de France|EDF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/depeches/2011/01/20/le-reacteur-sous-marin-nouveau-fleuron-de-l-industrie-nucleaire-francaise_3244_108_44231151.html|title=Le Monde.fr - Actualités et Infos en France et dans le monde|website=Le Monde.fr}}</ref> This unit of production is presented by its promoters as a modular development tool, which could be chosen by developing countries and areas of developed countries that need to compensate for an energy deficit.{{Citation needed|reason=This claim needs a reliable source|date=August 2017}}
