{{Use Indian English|date=July 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Krishna Pushkaram | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = 100px | image = File:Dhyana Buddha Ghat.jpg | alt = | caption = Dhyana Buddha Ghat in Amaravathi | status = Active | genre = [[Hindu festivals]] | begins = 12 August 2016 | ends = 23 August 2016 | frequency =once every 12 Years (lasts for 12 days) | venue = {{Collapsible list |framestyle=border:none; padding:0; <!--Hides borders and improves row spacing--> |title=Major [[ghats]] |[[Vijayawada]] |[[Machilipatnam]] |[[Vedhadri]] |[[Amaravathi (village), Guntur district|Amaravathi]]| [[Nagarjuna Sagar]]|[[Beechupalli]]|[[Krishna district]]|[[Rangapur, India|Rangapur]]||[[Alampur, Mahbubnagar|Alampur]] }} | location = [[Krishna River]] | coordinates = | country = [[India]] | first = | founder_name = | prev = 2016 | next = 2028 | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = [[South India]] | Website = | budget = | activity = Holy river dip and worship at the temples on the banks of the river | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | people = | member = | footnotes = }}
'''Krishna Pushkaralu''' is a festival of [[Krishna River|River Krishna]] which normally occurs once in every 12 years and is celebrated with much glory. The [[Pushkaram]] is observed for a period of 12 days from the time of entry of [[Jupiter]] into [[Virgo (astrology)|Virgo]] (''Kanya'' rasi). The festival is "theoretically" observed throughout the twelve months that the planet remains in that sign, but the first 12 days are considered most sacred as per the beliefs of Indians.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.krishnapushkaram.com/ |title= All about Krishna Pushkaralu 2016 |date=14 August 2016}}</ref> Pushkaram has been an age old practice in southern states Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka and Telangana. In 2016, the celebration started on 12 August and ended on 23 August. [[File:View of Pushkar Ghats.jpg|250px|thumb|left|Pushkar Ghats at Vijayawada ]] Ghats in Vijayawada: Padmavathi Ghat, Krishnaveni Ghat, Durga Ghat, Sithanagaram Ghat, Punnami Ghat, Bhavani Ghat, Pavithra Sangam (Ferry) Ghat
Ghats in Amaravathi: Shivalayam Ghat, Dhyana Buddha Ghat, Dharanikota Ghat
Ghats In Kurnool District: Patala Ganga Ghat (Srisailam), Sangameswaram River Ghat
Ghats in Gadwal, Mahaboob Nagar Juraala, Beechupally.
Ghats in Karnataka: Chikodi (Bagalkot), Raichur (Krishna Taluk)
